01:12:36.280 --> 01:12:38.446
that we'll talk about later
in the course concerning

01:12:38.446 --> 01:12:40.617
relativity.

01:12:40.617 --> 01:12:42.700
So far I think we've said
all we are going to say,

01:12:42.700 --> 01:12:45.324
unless the questions.

01:12:45.324 --> 01:12:46.740
I think we've said
all we're going

01:12:46.740 --> 01:12:48.860
to say about the
kinematic consequences

01:12:48.860 --> 01:12:51.260
of special relativity.

01:12:51.260 --> 01:12:54.070
And we're not going to be trying
to derive them, as I said.

01:12:54.070 --> 01:12:56.730
If you're interested,
