01:13:00.860 --> 01:13:03.430
from earlier years when
special relativity was

01:13:03.430 --> 01:13:05.916
included as a real topic.

01:13:05.916 --> 01:13:07.790
So certainly if you're
interested in learning

01:13:07.790 --> 01:13:09.600
about this and you
haven't already seen it,

01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:11.430
I'm happy to help you.

01:13:11.430 --> 01:13:14.180
But otherwise, it will
not be part of this course

01:13:14.180 --> 01:13:17.460
to discuss how these
three consequences

01:13:17.460 --> 01:13:20.740
of special relativity arise
from the basic postulates

01:13:20.740 --> 01:13:22.530
of special relativity.

01:13:22.530 --> 01:13:25.740
But later we will be saying
things that follow further

01:13:25.740 --> 01:13:29.720
along the line by
pursuing the consequences

01:13:29.720 --> 01:13:33.060
of special relativity
for momentum and energy,

01:13:33.060 --> 01:13:35.420
which will be important to us.

01:13:35.420 --> 01:13:38.530
The connection is the
important connection

01:13:38.530 --> 01:13:42.330
and simple connection
that energy and momentum

01:13:42.330 --> 01:13:44.110
are only interesting
to us if they're

01:13:44.110 --> 01:13:47.380
defined in a way which makes
them conserved quantities.

01:13:47.380 --> 01:13:49.960
That's why energy and momentum
are important in physics.

01:13:49.960 --> 01:13:52.250
Because for a closed
system, the total energy

01:13:52.250 --> 01:13:54.730
and the total momentum
do not change.

01:13:54.730 --> 01:13:56.740
Energy and momentum
can be transferred

01:13:56.740 --> 01:13:59.130
from one part of a
system to another.

01:13:59.130 --> 01:14:03.830
But energy and momentum cannot
be either made nor destroyed.

01:14:03.830 --> 01:14:07.760
Now if we took Newton's
definitions of energy

01:14:07.760 --> 01:14:14.700
and momentum, and used
relativistic kinematics, what

01:14:14.700 --> 01:14:17.070
we would find is
that if we looked

01:14:17.070 --> 01:14:19.750
at, say, a collision
of two particles,

01:14:19.750 --> 01:14:22.910
the Newtonian definitions
of energy and momentum,

01:14:22.910 --> 01:14:25.720
if we took those
seriously, would tell us

01:14:25.720 --> 01:14:29.115
what might happen
in a collision.

01:14:29.115 --> 01:14:30.990
Usually there's an angle
that's undetermined.

01:14:30.990 --> 01:14:33.315
But given an angle, it
determines everything else.

01:14:36.140 --> 01:14:39.490
If we used special
relativity to then describe

01:14:39.490 --> 01:14:43.147
what that same collision would
look like in a different frame,

01:14:43.147 --> 01:14:45.480
we would find that these
Newtonian definitions of energy

01:14:45.480 --> 01:14:48.240
and momentum would not be
conserved in the other frame,

01:14:48.240 --> 01:14:50.510
if they were conserved
in the first frame.

01:14:50.510 --> 01:14:53.440
The conservation laws
are dependent on what

01:14:53.440 --> 01:14:55.860
reference frame you're using.

01:14:55.860 --> 01:15:00.500
So what Einstein
amended was slightly

01:15:00.500 --> 01:15:04.950
modified definitions of
energy and momentum, which

01:15:04.950 --> 01:15:10.250
are determined by the criterion
that these slightly modified

01:15:10.250 --> 01:15:13.590
definitions of energy
and momentum should,

01:15:13.590 --> 01:15:15.950
if they are conserved
in one frame

01:15:15.950 --> 01:15:18.140
be also concerned in
any other frame, which

01:15:18.140 --> 01:15:21.710
are related by the relationships
to special relativity.

01:15:21.710 --> 01:15:24.040
So that's why it was
essential once one changed

01:15:24.040 --> 01:15:26.180
the kinematics of going
from one frame to another

01:15:26.180 --> 01:15:30.440
to also change the definitions
of energy and momentum

01:15:30.440 --> 01:15:34.540
so that the conservation laws
would hold in all frames using

01:15:34.540 --> 01:15:38.530
the new transformation equations
to get from frame to frame.

01:15:38.530 --> 01:15:40.120
And that's why
later in the course

01:15:40.120 --> 01:15:43.930
we will be introducing a
slightly modified, slightly

01:15:43.930 --> 01:15:47.100
non-Newtonian, definitions
of energy and momentum

01:15:47.100 --> 01:15:49.009
of moving particles.

